com.github.basking2.sdsai

Class RedBlackTree<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.basking2.sdsai.RedBlackTree<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<Key<E>>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Set

    public class RedBlackTree<E>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<Key<E>>
    An implementation of an Red Black Tree. Note, duplicate keys are allowed. The book Introduction to Algorithms by Cormen, Leiserson, Rivest and Stein was used for reference (and as such the algorithms may look JUST like theirs do). See section 13 in the 2nd edition.

    Here are the rules that dictate a Red-Black Tree's shape/look:

    • Every node is red or black.
    • The root is black.
    • Every leaf node is null (or NIL) and is a black node.
    • If a node is red, then both its children are black.
    • Every path from an internal node to a leaf node contains the same number of black nodes.

        public static final int ALL
        One of three modes that the add method can function with. This will add all objects to the tree.

      • NODUPOBJ

        public static final int NODUPOBJ
        One of three modes that the add method can function with. This will not add objects which are already in the tree. However, object that happen to generate the same key will be added.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • NODUPKEYS

        public static final int NODUPKEYS
        One of three modes that the add method can function with. This will not add object which generate the same key. This implies that no duplicate objects can be in the tree.

      • add

        public boolean add(Key<E> k,
                   int mode)
            throws DuplicateDataException
        This is just like add, but you can specify a mode. Use the flags provided.
        • ALL - all object are added.
        • NODUPOBJ - Do not add duplicate objects, but different object with the same key value will be added.
        • NODUPKEYS - Do not add object with the same keys.
        Throws:
        DuplicateDataException
